  "description": "Tore Hjalmar Lundberg was a Swedish lecturer and civil engineer. He was born on December 27, 1901, in Sallerup, Sweden. Tore married Gunvor Jerlström in 1932, and they had three children, Birgitta, Håkan, and Agneta. Tore graduated from Borås High School in 1920 and the Royal Institute of Technology in 1923. He studied abroad in the USA, Germany, Denmark, Belgium, and England at various times. Tore worked as an engineer in a hemp factory, sawmill, and construction engineering in Nairobi and Mombasa, Africa, from 1923 to 1931. He then pursued a career in education, teaching at various technical high schools and serving as a lecturer at Gothenburg Technical High School and the Chalmers University of Technology. Tore authored several works, including 'Strength of Materials' and 'Hydromechanics' for technical high schools, as well as contributing to the 'Swedish Engineer's Calendar'."
